def: To beat with a mall; to beat with something heavy; to bruise;to maul.
Germinating inside the pericarp, as the mangrove. Brande & C.
One of a body of native Algerian tirailleurs in the Frencharmy, dressed as a Turk. [Written also Turco.]
Causing animation; life-giving; inspiriting; rousing."Animating cries." Pope.-- An"i*ma`ting*ly, adv.
A displacement of an organ, esp. of the uterus, in such mannerthat its whole axis is directed further forward than usual.
Pertaining to tapestry produced in the so-called Gobelin works,which have been maintained by the French Government since 1667.
Relating to inquiry or inquisition; inquisitorial; also, of orpertaining to, or characteristic of, the Inquisition.All the inquisitional rigor . . . executed upon books. Milton.
A fixed star of the first magnitude in the left foot of theconstellation Orion. [Written also Regel.]
A cavalry raid; hence, a military expedition. [Obs.] Chaucer.
